<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> -Brief History-</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Family:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Whil is very tight-lipped about her family.  It isn't even known if her parents are alive any longer.  If questioned, she will use humor and change the subject (a talent she has become very skilled at).  She was on her own at least at the age of 14 and fell in with what could be termed the &quot;wrong crowd&quot;.  These people became her family.  Her street friends are loose-knit, but it is as close as she has to anything resembling family.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Religion:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
While she follows Bristlebane, she only does so half-heartedly.  She follows the beliefs of the rogue's god, but she doesn't feel any sense of duty or obligation to put herself out in the name of religion.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Personality:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Whil is outwardly friendly.  She has decided that sugar catches more flies than vinegar, but she will never truely open up to anyone who is not in her kin-group from her adolescent age.  One thing about Whil is she is very vain.  She has refused to take the woad markings that are part of Halas culture.  Green eyed with a sprinkling of freckles across her nose, she feels that her face is an asset, and to cover it would reduce the effectiveness of one of her &quot;tools&quot;.  She shuns hard work, but does have an extensive knowlege of the art of poison-craft.  She has been known to make great trips out of her way to gather ingredients for her brews.... and she has no compunction what so ever against slipping her hand into that fat purse at the cleric's waist.  A gal's gotta eat ya know!<br>
<br>
One word or phrase that sums Whilhamena up-<br>
Self-centered <p><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/thelizards/laur2.jpg><br>
