<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Aldrin of the Nexus</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (nee Aldrin Moonwalker)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Age:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> unknown, suspected to be at least 400.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Race:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> gnome<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Alignment:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Chaotic good<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Home City:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Highpass Hold (he has an apt there)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Class:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Wizard<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   -Brief History-</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Family:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
No one knows where Aldrin came from. For some, he's always been, for others, he's just appeared at the least opportune time. Stories can be found in Ak Anon claiming that his father was a mage and his mother an enchantress, but who they were and whatever happened to them remains a mystery. Aldrin has a very loose association of friends spanning all of Norrath and its moons which he might consider family, even though some might be considered mortal enemies to each other. Everywhere he goes he finds someone who knows him with affection, probably because he travels widely and likes everyone until they prove themselves unlikable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Religion:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Aldrin's chosen deity is Solusek Ro, purely for business purposes. His preferred diety might be Bristlebane, for he loves laughter and music, and is almost irresistably attracted to rogues and bards.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Personality:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Emotionally, Aldrin is six and three-quarter years old, in spite of his possible age. No one knows why he developed his characteristic lisp, but it does cause him exceptional embarassment and he can be brought to tears by those cruel enough to make fun of him for it. <br>
Aldrin loves life, and is fascinated by the people he encounters. He doesn't really view anyone as bad, until they try to hurt him or someone he likes. He is indescriminate in this; he's been known to challenge Al Kabor himself over insults directed at a recently acquired friend.<br>
Ultimately courageous, Aldrin too often volunteers to take the brunt of damage in  a battle to spare his companions the pain and risk of death that such activities often entail. When a battle goes badly, and evacuation is not an option, he's been known to cast area effect spells or otherwise aggrevate his opponents in an attempt to buy time for his companions to escape or regroup and heal. Rarely does this work. <br>
Aldrin's secret dream is to someday become a barbarian, preferably a warrior. He is totally fascinated by the harsh yet compassionate lifestyle forced upon them by their native climate. The sheer size of barbarians might have something to do with it as well. <br>
If he can be located nowhere else, he often can be found in Halas, in the dog pens petting and playing with the Barbarian's True Companions. The dogs, with their instinctive recognition of good and evil, always welcome him into their company, and have even been known to growl menacingly at their master if s/he should wander too close while Aldrin is present.<br>
<br>
One word to describe Aldrin:<br>
<br>
Aldrin.<br>
<br>
(addendum: anyone wishing to learn the nature of Aldrin should read Rudyard Kipling's &quot;Wee Willie Winkie&quot;)<br>
